description: Five people in possession of 306 kilograms of gold were arrested on Thursday, shortly after an attack on a precious metals processing company. They were charged on Monday.

headline: Cement maker Lafarge goes on trial in France for 'funding terrorism' in Syria
description: The company and eight former employees are standing trial for having paid money to jihadist groups to keep a plant in Syria running. Unusually, Lafarge had already pleaded guilty to this charge before US courts in 2022.

headline: How New York became a nightmare for Airbnb
description: 'The Airbnb Ogre' (6/6). For the past two years, short-term tourist rentals have effectively been banned in the American metropolis as the result of a massively complex regulatory overhaul. The platform is now hoping, without much optimism, to see the rules eased after the municipal elections on Tuesday.

headline: Laurent Mauvignier wins 2025 Prix Goncourt for 'La Maison vide'
description: The writer won France's most prestigious literary prize for his monumental novel, a reinvention of his family's history across four generations, set in a rural French house.

headline: The French cities utterly transformed by Airbnb
description: 'The Airbnb Ogre' (3/6). Turning an apartment into short-term tourist accommodation may seem harmless. But on a large scale, it ends up transforming entire cities and daily life for their residents. France's politicians are trying to crack down on the system.

headline: Svalbard, the fastest-warming place on Earth
description: 'Our planet at +1.5°C' (1/6). The Norwegian archipelago has warmed by 4°C over the past 30 years. Landslides and thawing permafrost threaten the population, whose way of life is highly greenhouse gas-intensive.
